crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Identifies the 64 bit API hashing function used by Metasploit. This has been re-used by many other malware families.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Elastic Security

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is classified as malicious. It uses dynamic API resolution by walking the PEB, hashing module and function names, and comparing them to pre-calculated values to find their addresses. This is a common obfuscation technique to hide imports. It then allocates a memory region with execute permissions (VirtualAlloc with PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE) and copies a payload into it for execution (shellcode). The presence of a section with Read-Write-Execute permissions (.sjmf) further supports this conclusion, indicating the binary is likely a packer or loader.
